Article.ArticleTitle: [Seed germinative characteristics and embryo development of Schisandra chinensis (Turcz.) Bail].

AbstractText: To detect the germinative character of S. chinensis seeds.
Using low temperature and gibberellin treatment.

The breach rate of seeds was increased by both low temperature and gibberellin, but the breach on different seeds appeared untidy, which showing a character. The embryo development is normal before breaching and increased in volume rapidly after breaching.
The bypoplasia of embryos is not the primary reason for long dormancy of the seeds.
